  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan asked us to write one long entry looking back at the whole first semester, so here is my honest attempt.",
      "zh": "潘老師要我們寫一篇長長的回顧，看看整個第一學期，所以這就是我誠實的嘗試。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Whenever I look back at my early entries, I notice how nervous and formal I sounded, almost like I was writing for a stranger.",
      "zh": "每次回頭看我早期的日記，我都注意到自己聽起來又緊張又拘謹，好像是在寫給一個陌生人看的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Now I write wherever I happen to be, whether that is my desk, the couch, or even the bus, and it feels much more natural.",
      "zh": "現在我不管人在哪都能寫，不管是我的書桌、沙發，甚至公車上，感覺自然多了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I used to think a diary needed a strict daily schedule, but I seldom write every single day, and that turns out to be perfectly fine.",
      "zh": "我以前以為日記需要嚴格的每日排程，但我很少每天寫，而事實證明這樣完全沒問題。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Some entries came from real difficulty, like the day our classroom fish died, and some came from silly, easy topics, like William's robot costume.",
      "zh": "有些篇章來自真正的難過，像是教室的魚過世那天，也有些來自輕鬆好寫的主題，像是 William 的機器人裝。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice, whom I barely knew at the start of the semester, is now somewhat close to being my best friend, which I never expected in September.",
      "zh": "學期一開始我幾乎不認識的 Bernice，現在已經算是我頗親近的好朋友了，這是我九月的時候完全沒料到的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William, whose favorite topic changes constantly, has appeared in almost every single one of my entries, either causing trouble or being surprisingly wise.",
      "zh": "興趣話題一直在變的 William，幾乎出現在我每一篇日記裡，不是在闖禍，就是意外地很有智慧。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Throughout the semester, Sophia's rules stayed exactly the same, though I have learned to follow them without complaining quite so much.",
      "zh": "整個學期 Sophia 的規矩都完全沒變，不過我已經學會遵守它們，不再抱怨得那麼多了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I used to think school was mainly about tests and grades; now I understand it is also about the small, ordinary moments between classes.",
      "zh": "我以前以為上學主要是為了考試跟成績；現在我明白它也包含了下課之間那些平凡的小片刻。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Some classmates I barely spoke to at first became fellow club members, and a few remain simply names I recognize but do not truly know.",
      "zh": "有些一開始我幾乎沒講過話的同學，後來變成了社團夥伴，也有些依然只是我認得名字但不真正認識的人。"
    },
    {
      "en": "My handwriting is somewhat better than it was in September, though it is far from what I would call neat or careful.",
      "zh": "我的字比九月的時候好一點了，不過離我認為整齊或工整還差得遠。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I no longer think \"diary\" is a shameful word, though I will admit it took the entire semester to feel that way, not just one lucky day.",
      "zh": "我不再覺得「日記」是個可恥的字了，不過我得承認，這種感覺是花了整整一學期才建立起來的，不是靠某一天幸運就達成的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Perhaps the biggest change is simple: I now actually want to write, rather than seeing it as required homework I must finish.",
      "zh": "或許最大的改變很簡單：我現在是真的想寫，而不是把它當成必須完成的功課。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Until this semester, I had no real reason to pay attention to ordinary days; now I understand they are, quite honestly, most of my life.",
      "zh": "在這學期之前，我完全沒有理由去注意平凡的日子；現在我明白，老實說，它們就是我人生的大部分。"
    },
    {
      "en": "So, to whoever reads this notebook someday, near or far: this was my very first semester of keeping a diary, and I regret none of it.",
      "zh": "所以，未來不管誰讀到這本筆記本，不管在近處還是遠處：這是我寫日記的第一個學期，而我一點都不後悔。"
    }
  ],
